                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Chennai, June 27 (PTI): Ten children from Guyana, who had not been permitted to leave a hospital here for non-settlement of bills for their heart surgeries, were allowed to return home after an NGO, which sponsored their treatment, and the hospital reached an agreement today.           
	The Guyana-based NGO, Kids First Fund, run by Varshnie Singh, former First Lady of the Carribean Republic, had agreed to settle the bills within six months for surgeries performed at Frontier Lifeline Hospital earlier this month.           gh had tried to leave the hospital with the children yesterday but officials asked her to clear the bills first.           gh said her NGO has been sending children to the hospital for treatment for the last four years. She said the organisation cleared the bills by conducting a fund-raising event with the children in London, on their way back to Guyana.                  
	 Mumbai: A fire broke out in the basement of the heritage wing of the Taj Palace hotel in Mumbai on Saturday. A Taj spokesperson said a short circuit caused the fire. No major damage was reported at the hotel, one of the sites of the 26/11 attacks.                  
	 London (PTI): The family of a Hindu priest living at the Indian Community Centre in north Belfast came under a racial attack from a group of youths on June 15 night. The gang tried to break down the centres door and threw stones. The priests wife was alone at home during the attack. Police have beefed up security at the centre.                  
	 Mumbai (PTI): The mother of a teenaged US girl who tested positive for swine flu on Friday was admitted to a Mumbai hospital on Saturday with symptoms of the H1N1 influenza. The two of them had come to Thane from Virginia to meet relatives. The mother has been quarantined.                                                                                                                           
